holotype and paratypes. (151) body; (152) head and pronotum; (153) antenna and fore tarsus, showing the enlarged hamus (black arrow); (154) mesonotum; (155) pelta, showing the multiple campaniform sensilla (black arrows); (156) spermatheca; (157) male sternite VIII, showing weak spots, which may be the pore plates (white arrows); (158) metanotum.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="58.[151,1437,151,1112]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">
